channel.title: Unnamed Empire
channel.description:
Well we are a growing empire, so I think we need a thread to keep track of what's going on here.
More information later.
Current Members:
Davidi2 (Founder) Frell (Founder) Tom5001 (Tom_BETA) nativemule binkiss Kracky ramen (rixisthebest/rix_) SteamTempest (TabbyKiller) Joelyrolly (Si Force) Badger41 xryz huskit
For members, [img]http://i.imgur.com/ua3zH.png[/img] [img]http://[img]http://img707.imageshack.us/img707/5474/citynew.png[/img][/img]
Light Red = Davidi2's property (please don't build in here without my permission) Yellow = Frell's Tower Dark Red = Kracky's House Tan = Ramen's underground structure entrance Not visible (will get a picture later) Tom5001's Monument
Current Tasks: - Finish the man-made lake with dock and hook it somehow to the ocean nearby - Finish the walls - New members create houses ~ don't forget a sign with your name within 2 blocks of your door!

item.dc:creator: @xryz xryz
item.description:
@xryz wrote:

[quote=“LilXCj, post:173, topic:393179”][quote author=xryz link=topic=490349.msg3595542#msg3595542 date=1305043777]

We are never, ever, ever, having a map reset again. Ever.

What happens if we have to do one later on? Like, if the map gets overwritten or something?

If we don’t have a choice, then we don’t have a choice. But hopefully that will never happen either.

how big does the map get? i havent hosted a mc server so idk how big our map gets. ik the single player maps are 10’s of megs for a small map compared to the servers map. an idea i had was place a redundent backup of the map on one or multiple dropbox accounts. dropbox isnt open source but the sync part is nice. but having redundent backups of the server will hopefully save that problem we had from the last map.
[/quote]

It gets big because people like to move outwards. The last map was 500+ MB[/quote]

ok. well a dropbox account is 2 gb free, and its not hard to get multiple accounts and share a folder. i havent did much(host video files to play on a site in development, also i have a html file on one to show u can host a simple website from it without too much work.) with dropbox accounts. i have 2 with one sharing a folder with the other. im guessing the one sharing the folder would be able to give permission to the other it is sharing with so the 2nd account could use all 4 gigs of storage. 2gigs isnt a lot now a days. how big would the ma[ have to be to use up 2 or more gigs?
